HEADWORD: Multiplicity
<hw>Mul`ti*plic"ity</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>multiplicit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being
multiple, manifold, or various; a state of being many; a multitude;
<as>as, a <ex>multiplicity</ex> of thoughts or objects</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>multiplicity</xex> of goods.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

